defaultIt has been a busy and challenging first year in office as Police and Crime Commissioner for Avon and Somerset. I have
default been clear that I see my role as fulfilling three prime purposes:- 
defaultThe overriding impression from the first year is the public response that I have received – I have had over 20 times the level of correspondence that the Police Authority had in its last year of operation. Local people do raise their policing issues, concerns and comments with me and I have worked 
defaultclosely
default with the local Constabulary to ensure that these are taken into account.
